A millenia ago, the king of Telluria at the time created
a backup plan in the case that the two champions sent to
defeat \c[18]Apocalypse\c[0] may fail in their mission.
A group of powerful mages known as the Last Stand.
The champions did indeed fail, but the mages foresaw
\c[18]Apocalypse\c[0]'s plan to attack Telluria Castle. They

...they cast an extremely powerful magical seal. A

In the years after the Great Collapse, chaos broke out across
the land. Entire regions and cities were destroyed, and the
political landscape shifted as a result of those looking to
take advantage of the Overworld's collective suffering.
With the royal military occupied with defending what
remained of the kingdom, no force could be spared to
stop insurgents and crime lords from taking over
As the centuries went on, crime rates continued to lower.
However, the effects of the initial takeovers can still
be seen today in regions such as the Blazing Sands.
Today, Telluria stands strong. The mainland is united,
close ties have been kept with Adon, and Arcanus has
been left to prosper on its own. Times have improved.
There are still problems. Crime still runs rampant in
the aforementioned Blazing Sands, and the outer reaches
of the mainland are threatened by criminals and monsters.
Still, no matter what, Tellurians do not back down
to a threat. We will continue fighting the good fight
until there's no more fight to be fought!
